Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of affray. I would like to take this opportunity to briefly explain the circumstances surrounding my involvement in this incident.

On the day in question, I had just discovered that my boyfriend had been unfaithful to me. Fueled by emotions and hurt, I made the impulsive decision to confront him at a bar where I knew he would be. In a moment of anger and frustration, I threatened him by mentioning the possibility of possessing a firearm. It is important to note that I do not own a gun nor have any means of obtaining one.

During the course of the confrontation, I admit to slapping my boyfriend in the face. However, I did not cause any further harm to him or anyone else present at the bar. I understand and acknowledge that my actions caused fear and distress among the individuals who witnessed the incident, and for that, I am truly sorry.

I am aware that I should have taken a more composed approach in handling the situation. My behavior in the bar lasted approximately 15 minutes before I ultimately decided to leave and go home. I now realize the gravity of my actions and deeply regret the distress I caused to others.

Your Honor, I would like to bring your attention to several mitigating factors that I believe should be taken into consideration. Firstly, I have no prior criminal record, demonstrating that this incident is an isolated and uncharacteristic event in my life. Furthermore, I am currently undergoing therapy once a week to address my emotional well-being and work on improving myself. This displays my sincere commitment to personal growth and change.

In conclusion, I am pleading guilty to the offense of affray, fully accepting the responsibility for my actions. I understand the impact of my behavior and the fear it may have caused, and I assure the court that such actions will not be repeated in the future. I respectfully ask for leniency in sentencing, taking into account the mitigating circumstances presented.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

Sincerely,
Chloe Mills

