1141
Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of affray. I would like to take this opportunity to explain the circumstances surrounding my involvement in this incident and provide relevant information about my character.

On the day in question, I discovered that my boyfriend had been unfaithful to me. Overcome by a surge of emotions and hurt, I made the impulsive decision to confront him at a bar where I knew he would be. In a moment of anger and frustration, I threatened him by mentioning the possibility of possessing a firearm. However, I want to emphasize that I do not own a gun or have any means of obtaining one.

During the confrontation, I admit to slapping my boyfriend in the face. I deeply regret my actions, but I want to clarify that I did not cause any further harm to him or anyone else present at the bar. I understand the fear and distress I may have caused to those who witnessed the incident, and for that, I am genuinely sorry.

I acknowledge that my behavior in the bar lasted approximately 15 minutes before I decided to leave and go home. Reflecting on this incident, I realize the gravity of my actions and the need for me to handle difficult situations in a more responsible and composed manner.

While I have no previous criminal record, I would like to bring to your attention that I actively participate in therapy sessions once a week. Through my therapy, I am actively working on personal growth and improving myself. Attending therapy underscores my commitment to self-improvement and ensuring that I learn from my mistakes.

In conclusion, I accept full responsibility for my actions on that day and express my sincere remorse. I understand the need for accountability and assure you that I am committed to making better choices in the future. I appreciate your time and consideration.

Sincerely,
Chloe Mills

